<TITLE> Journalist Ahmed Faruq Hasan, 48, dies of heart attack </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 6 (bdnews24.com)  Ahmed Faruq Hasan, deputy editor of the Daily Jugantor, died on Sunday. He was 48. He died of cardiac arrest at around 11pm. "He suffered a heart attack while he was in the office. He died on the way to hospital," Rafiqul Islam Ratan, chief correspondent of the Daily Jugantor, told bdnews24.com. Doctors at Dhaka Medical College Hospital declared him dead on arrival. Known throughout the news world, Faruq was founding news editor of the Daily Ajker Kagoj. He also held the post of news editor at the Daily Bhorer Kagoj, Banglabazar and Manabjami
